ent%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fweb-series%2Fnews%2Fkorean%2Fyg-entertainment-denies-ahyeons-exit-from-babymonster-report%2Farticleshow%2F105249810.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22S%20Jaishankar%20Asks%20Canada%20To%20Give%20Evidence%20In%20Hardeep%20Nijjar%20Killing%20Case%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EExternal%20Affairs%20Minister%20S%20Jaishankar%20has%20said%20that%20India%20is%20not%20ruling%20out%20an%20investigation%20into%20Canada's%20allegations%20about%20the%20involvement%20of%20the%20Indian%20government's%20agents%20in%20the%20killing%20of%20a%20Khalistani%20terrorist%20in%20that%20country%20but%20wants%20it%20to%20provide%20evidence%20to%20back%20its%20claims.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Jaishankar%20made%20the%20comments%20on%20Wednesday%20in%20response%20to%20questions%20during%20a%20conversation%20with%20veteran%20journalist%20Lionel%20Barber%20titled%20'How%20a%20Billion%20People%20See%20the%20World'%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20have%20a%20reason%20to%20make%20such%20an%20allegation%20please%20share%20the%20evidence%20because%20we%20are%20not%20ruling%20out%20an%20investigation%E2%80%A6%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Jaishankar%2C%20who%20is%20here%20on%20a%20five-day%20official%20visit%20to%20the%20UK%2C%20said%20while%20responding%20to%20a%20question.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20emphasised%20that%20Canada%20has%20not%20shared%20any%20evidence%20with%20India%20to%20support%20its%20allegations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ties%20between%20India%20and%20Canada%20came%20under%20severe%20strain%20following%20Canadian%20Prime%20Minister%20Justin%20Trudeau's%20allegations%20in%20September%20of%20a%20%26quot%3Bpotential%26quot%3B%20involvement%20of%20Indian%20agents%20in%20the%20killing%20of%20Khalistani%20terrorist%20Hardeep%20Singh%20Nijjar%20on%20June%2018%20in%20British%20Columbia.%20India%20had%20designated%20Nijjar%20as%20a%20terrorist%20in%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20has%20rejected%20Trudeau's%20allegations%20as%20%26quot%3Babsurd%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bmotivated%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Jaishankar%20said%20that%20freedom%20of%20speech%20and%20freedom%20of%20expression%20comes%20with%20a%20certain%20responsibility%20and%20the%20misuse%20of%20those%20freedoms%20and%20the%20toleration%20of%20that%20misuse%20for%20political%20purposes%20would%20be%20very%20wrong%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20pro-Khalistani%20activities%20in%20Canada.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Jaishankar%20said%20that%20he%20was%20in%20touch%20with%20his%20Canadian%20counterpart%20Melanie%20Joly%20on%20the%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20recalled%20the%20attacks%20on%20the%20High%20Commission%20of%20India%20in%20Canada%2C%20or%20smoke%20bomb%20attacks%20on%20the%20High%20Commission%20and%20Consulate%20General%2C%20and%20said%20Indian%20diplomats%20were%20intimidated%20in%20public%2C%20with%20no%20action%20from%20the%20Canadian%20authorities%20against%20culprits.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20week%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Trudeau%20underlined%20that%20a%20%26quot%3Bfight%26quot%3B%20with%20India%20was%20not%20something%20Canada%20wanted%20to%20be%20having%20right%20now%20but%20reiterated%20his%20allegations%20and%20said%20Ottawa%20wants%20to%20%26quot%3Bwork%20constructively%26quot%3B%20with%20New%20Delhi%20on%20this%20%26quot%3Bvery%20serious%20matter%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EForeign%20Secretary%20Vinay%20Kwatra%20said%20India%20has%20conveyed%20to%20the%20US%20side%20its%20serious%20concerns%20over%20increasing%20activities%20of%20pro-Khalistani%20elements%20in%20Canada.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BInsofar%20as%20Canada%20is%20concerned%2C%20we%20have%20been%20having%20very%20consistent%20conversations%20with%20all%20our%20friends%20and%20partners.%20Our%20position%20on%20this%20matter%20has%20been%20enunciated%20and%20explained%20in%20full%20detail%20on%20multiple%20occasions%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Kwatra%20said%20in%20New%20Delhi%20recently.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDays%20after%20Trudeau's%20allegations%20in%20September%2C%20India%20temporarily%20suspended%20the%20issuance%20of%20visas%20to%20Canadian%20citizens%20and%20asked%20Ottawa%20to%20downsize%20its%20diplomatic%20presence%20in%20the%20country%20to%20ensure%20parity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20resumed%20some%20visa%20services%20in%20Canada%20last%20month%2C%20more%20than%20a%20month%20after%20they%20were%20suspended.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20China%2C%20Mr%20Jaishankar%20said%20that%20the%202020%20deadly%20clash%20in%20the%20Galwan%20Valley%20has%20vitiated%20the%20relationship%20between%20the%20two%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20China%20did%20not%20adhere%20to%20the%20agreements%20of%201993%20and%201996%20not%20to%20amass%20troops%20at%20the%20Line%20of%20Actual%20Control%20as%20he%20asserted%20that%20such%20acts%20of%20not%20following%20pacts%20have%20consequences%20in%20terms%20of%20credibility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700108220000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-09%2Fg5mlpse8_s-jaishankar_625x300_27_September_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fhardeep-singh-nijjar-killing-s-jaishankar-asks-canada-to-provide-evidence-4577831%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22S%20Jaishankar%20has%20said%20that%20India%20is%20not%20ruling%20out%20an%20investigation%20into%20Canada's%20allegations%20about%20the%20involvement%20of%20the%20Indian%20government's%20agents%20in%20the%20killing%20of%20a%20Khalistani%20terrorist.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fhardeep-singh-nijjar-killing-s-jaishankar-asks-canada-to-provide-evidence-4577831%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fhardeep-singh-nijjar-killing-s-jaishankar-asks-canada-to-provide-evidence-4577831%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fhardeep-singh-nijjar-killing-s-jaishankar-asks-canada-to-provide-evidence-4577831%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22N.%20Sankaraiah%3A%20One%20Hundred%20Years%20a%20Revolutionary%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F16092418%2F04a-2013-JULY-20-2-PS-Sankariah-Nine_decad.max-1400x1120-1.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EN.%20Sankaraiah%20was%20a%20freedom%20fighter%20and%20Marxist%20activist.%20He%20was%20one%20of%20the%20founding%20members%20of%20the%20Communist%20Party%20of%20India.%20He%20passed%20away%20yesterday%2C%20November%2015%2C%202023%2C%20at%20101%20years%20of%20age.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20crowds%20rushed%20out%20on%20to%20the%20streets%20of%20Thoothukudi%20town%20%E2%80%93%20as%20they%20did%20across%20many%20parts%20of%20Tamil%20Nadu%20%E2%80%93%20a%20very%20young%20boy%20ran%20out%20to%20join%20them.%20In%20moments%20he%20was%20part%20of%20the%20protest%2C%20shouting%20radical%20slogans.%20%E2%80%9CYou%20may%20not%20know%20or%20realise%20that%20today%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20tells%20us%2C%20%E2%80%9Cbut%20the%20execution%20of%20Bhagat%20Singh%20was%20an%20emotional%20turning%20point%20for%20the%20freedom%20struggle%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu.%20People%20were%20appalled%20and%20so%20many%20were%20in%20tears.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20was%20just%209%20years%20old%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20chuckles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20he%20is%2099%20years%20old%20(July%2015%2C%202020)%2C%20but%20retains%20the%20fire%20and%20spirit%20that%20made%20him%20a%20freedom%20fighter%2C%20an%20underground%20revolutionary%2C%20writer%2C%20orator%20and%20radical%20intellectual.%20A%20man%20who%20stepped%20out%20of%20a%20British%20jail%20on%20August%2014%2C%201947.%20%E2%80%9COn%20that%20day%2C%20the%20judge%20came%20to%20the%20central%20prison%20and%20released%20us.%20We%20had%20been%20acquitted%20in%20the%20Madurai%20conspiracy%20case.%20I%20just%20came%20out%20of%20Madurai%20central%20prison%20and%20joined%20the%20freedom%20procession%20rally.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBatting%20on%20100%2C%20N.%20Sankaraiah%20remains%20intellectually%20active%2C%20still%20delivers%20lectures%20and%20talks%20and%2C%20as%20late%20as%202018%2C%20travelled%20from%20his%20home%20in%20Chrompet%2C%20a%20Chennai%20suburb%20%E2%80%93%20where%20we%E2%80%99re%20interviewing%20him%20%E2%80%93%20to%20address%20the%20Tamil%20Nadu%20Progressive%20Writers%20and%20Artists%20meet%20in%20Madurai.%20The%20man%20who%20never%20completed%20his%20graduation%20because%20of%20his%20involvement%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20struggle%20for%20freedom%20went%20on%20to%20author%20several%20political%20tracts%2C%20booklets%2C%20pamphlets%20and%20journalistic%20articles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENarasimhalu%20Sankariah%20came%20close%20to%20getting%20that%20BA%20in%20History%20though%2C%20at%20The%20American%20College%2C%20Madurai%2C%20missing%20out%20on%20his%20final%20exams%20in%201941%20by%20just%20two%20weeks.%20%E2%80%9CI%20was%20joint%20secretary%20of%20the%20college%20students%E2%80%99%20union.%E2%80%9D%20And%20a%20bright%20pupil%20who%20founded%20a%20poetry%20society%20on%20campus%20while%20also%20representing%20the%20college%20in%20football.%20He%20was%20very%20active%20in%20the%20anti-British%20Raj%20movements%20of%20the%20time.%20%E2%80%9CDuring%20my%20college%20days%2C%20I%20befriended%20many%20people%20with%20left-inclined%20ideologies.%20I%20understood%20that%20social%20reform%20would%20not%20be%20complete%20without%20Indian%20Independence.%E2%80%9D%20By%20age%2017%2C%20he%20was%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Communist%20Party%20of%20India%20(then%20banned%20and%20underground).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20remembers%20the%20attitude%20of%20the%20American%20College%20as%20being%20positive.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20director%20and%20a%20few%20of%20the%20faculty%20were%20Americans%2C%20the%20rest%20Tamilians.%20They%20were%20supposed%20to%20be%20neutral%2C%20but%20they%20were%20not%20pro-British.%20Student%20activities%20were%20allowed%20there%E2%80%A6.%E2%80%9D%20In%201941%2C%20a%20meeting%20was%20held%20in%20Madurai%20to%20condemn%20the%20arrest%20of%20an%20Annamalai%20University%20student%2C%20Meenakshi%2C%20for%20taking%20part%20in%20anti-British%20protests.%20%E2%80%9CAnd%20we%20issued%20a%20pamphlet.%20Our%20hostel%20rooms%20were%20raided%2C%20and%20Narayanaswami%20(my%20friend)%20was%20arrested%20for%20having%20a%20pamphlet.%20Later%20we%20held%20a%20protest%20meeting%20to%20condemn%20his%20arrest%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FxpPK1bJC0Nc%3Ffeature%3Doembed%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22840%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Sankariah%20and%20the%20struggle%20for%20India%E2%80%99s%20freedom%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22473%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAfter%20that%2C%20the%20British%20arrested%20me%2C%20on%20February%2028%2C%201941.%20It%20was%2015%20days%20before%20my%20final%20exams.%20I%20never%20came%20back%2C%20never%20completed%20my%20BA.%E2%80%9D%20Describing%20the%20moment%20of%20his%20arrest%20he%20would%20say%2C%20decades%20later%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20was%20proud%20to%20go%20to%20jail%20for%20India%E2%80%99s%20freedom%2C%20to%20be%20part%20of%20the%20Independence%20struggle.%20This%20was%20the%20only%20thought%20in%20my%20head.%E2%80%9D%20Nothing%20about%20a%20destroyed%20career.%20That%20was%20in%20line%20with%20one%20of%20his%20favourite%20slogans%20of%20radical%20youth%20of%20that%20time%3A%20%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20not%20job%20hunters%3B%20we%20are%20freedom%20hunters.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAfter%20spending%2015%20days%20in%20Madurai%20Jail%2C%20I%20was%20sent%20to%20Vellore%20prison.%20At%20that%20time%2C%20many%20people%20from%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20Andhra%20Pradesh%2C%20Kerala%20were%20also%20detained%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CComrade%20A.%20K.%20Gopalan%20%5Blegendary%20communist%20party%20leader%20from%20Kerala%5D%20was%20arrested%20in%20Trichy%20for%20organising%20an%20event.%20Comrades%20Imbichi%20Bava%20from%20Kerala%2C%20V.%20Subbiah%2C%20Jeevanandham%2C%20were%20also%20arrested%20during%20the%20event.%20They%20were%20all%20there%20in%20Vellore%20prison.%20The%20Madras%20government%20intended%20to%20divide%20us%20into%20two%20groups%2C%20one%20of%20which%20would%20get%20%E2%80%98C%E2%80%99%20type%20ration%2C%20which%20they%20gave%20only%20to%20the%20criminal%20convicts.%20We%20staged%20a%2019-day%20hunger%20strike%20against%20this%20system.%20By%20day%2010%2C%20they%20divided%20us%20into%20two%20groups.%20I%20was%20just%20a%20student%20then.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20very%20surprised%20Inspector%20General%20of%20Prisons%20who%20dropped%20in%20on%20Sankariah%E2%80%99s%20cell%20to%20find%20the%20teenager%20reading%20Maxim%20Gorky%E2%80%99s%C2%A0%3Cem%3EMother%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E.%20%E2%80%9C%E2%80%98On%20the%20tenth%20day%20that%20you%20are%20on%20hunger%20strike%2C%20you%20are%20reading%20literature%20%E2%80%93%20Gorky%E2%80%99s%C2%A0%3Cem%3EMother%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3F%E2%80%99%20he%20asked%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Sankariah%2C%20eyes%20gleaming%20with%20fun%20at%20the%20recollection.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20famous%20personalities%20held%20at%20the%20time%20there%2C%20in%20a%20separate%20jail%2C%20included%20%E2%80%9CKamarajar%20%5BK.%20Kamaraj%2C%20later%20chief%20minister%20of%20Madras%20State%20%E2%80%93%20now%20Tamil%20Nadu%20%E2%80%93%20from%201954-63%5D%2C%20Pattabhi%20Sitaramayya%20%5BCongress%20president%20soon%20after%20Independence%5D%2C%20and%20many%20others.%20However%2C%20they%20were%20in%20another%20yard%2C%20another%20jail.%20The%20congressmen%20did%20not%20participate%20in%20the%20hunger%20strike.%20Their%20line%20was%3A%20%E2%80%98We%20are%20bound%20by%20Mahatma%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20advice%E2%80%99.%20Which%20was%3A%20%E2%80%98don%E2%80%99t%20have%20any%20stir%20in%20jail%E2%80%99.%20However%2C%20the%20government%20made%20some%20concessions.%20We%20stopped%20our%20hunger%20strike%20on%20day%2019.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F16092354%2FScreenshot-2023-11-16-at-9.22.45.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F16092354%2FScreenshot-2023-11-16-at-9.22.45.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F16092354%2FScreenshot-2023-11-16-at-9.22.45-300x269.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F16092354%2FScreenshot-2023-11-16-at-9.22.45-1024x917.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-684993%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221075%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ETop%20left%3A%20Sankariah%20at%20his%20party%E2%80%99s%20state%20committee%20office%20in%20the%20mid-90s.%20Top%20right%3A%20At%20a%20public%20meeting%20(first%20person%2C%20front%20corner)%20addressed%20by%20his%20old%20comrade%20P.%20Ramamurti%20in%20the%201980s%2C%20Bottom%20row%3A%20Addressing%20an%20anti-corruption%20meeting%20in%20Chennai%20in%202011.%20Photo%3A%20S.%20Gavaskar%2F%20People%E2%80%99s%20Archive%20of%20Rural%20India%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20their%20strong%20differences%20on%20issues%2C%20says%20Sankariah%2C%20%E2%80%9CKamarajar%20was%20a%20very%20good%20friend%20of%20the%20communists.%20His%20companions%20sharing%20a%20room%20in%20the%20jail%20%E2%80%93%20from%20Madurai%20and%20Tirunelveli%20%E2%80%93%20were%20also%20communists.%20I%20used%20to%20be%20very%20close%20to%20Kamarajar.%20He%20intervened%20more%20than%20once%20to%20try%20and%20end%20our%20ill-treatment.%20But%20of%20course%2C%20there%20were%20huge%20arguments%20in%20the%20jail%20%5Bbetween%20congressmen%20and%20communists%5D%2C%20especially%20when%20the%20German-Soviet%20war%20broke%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CA%20while%20later%2C%20eight%20of%20us%20were%20transferred%20to%20the%20jail%20in%20Rajahmundry%20%5Bnow%20in%20Andhra%20Pradesh%5D%20and%20placed%20in%20a%20separate%20yard%20there.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBy%20April%201942%2C%20the%20government%20released%20all%20the%20students%20%E2%80%93%20except%20me.%20The%20head%20warden%20came%20and%20asked%3A%20%E2%80%98Who%20is%20Sankariah%3F%E2%80%99%20and%20then%20informed%20us%20that%20everybody%20was%20released%20%E2%80%93%20other%20than%20me.%20For%20a%20month%2C%20I%20was%20in%20solitary%20confinement%20and%20had%20the%20entire%20yard%20to%20myself!%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20were%20he%20and%20the%20others%20charged%20with%3F%20%E2%80%9CNo%20formal%20charges%2C%20only%20detention.%20Every%20six%20months%20they%20would%20send%20you%20a%20written%20notice%2C%20stating%20the%20reasons%20why%20you%20were%20grounded.%20The%20reasons%20would%20be%3A%20sedition%2C%20communist%20party%20activities%2C%20etc.%20We%20would%20submit%20a%20response%20to%20it%20to%20a%20committee%20%E2%80%93%20and%20the%20committee%20would%20reject%20it.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOddly%20enough%2C%20%E2%80%9Cmy%20friends%20who%20were%20released%20from%20Rajahmundry%20jail%20met%20Kamarajar%20at%20Rajahmundry%20station%20%E2%80%93%20he%20was%20returning%20from%20Calcutta%20%5BKolkata%5D.%20When%20he%20learned%20I%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20released%2C%20he%20wrote%20a%20letter%20to%20the%20chief%20secretary%20of%20Madras%20stating%20that%20I%20should%20be%20transferred%20back%20to%20Vellore%20jail.%20He%20wrote%20me%20a%20letter%20also.%20I%20was%20transferred%20a%20month%20later%20to%20Vellore%20jail%20%E2%80%93%20where%20I%20was%20with%20200%20other%20colleagues.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20one%20of%20his%20many%20trips%20to%20several%20prisons%2C%20Sankariah%20would%20also%20meet%20R.%20Venkataraman%2C%20the%20future%20president%20of%20India.%20%E2%80%9CHe%20was%20with%20the%20Communist%20Party%20of%20India%20in%20jail%2C%20a%20member%20in%201943.%20Later%2C%20of%20course%2C%20he%20went%20on%20to%20join%20the%20Congress%20party.%20Nonetheless%2C%20we%20did%20work%20together%20for%20several%20years.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F16092409%2F03-PS-Sankariah-Nine_decades_a_revolutionary.width-1440.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F16092409%2F03-PS-Sankariah-Nine_decades_a_revolutionary.width-1440.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F16092409%2F03-PS-Sankariah-Nine_decades_a_revolutionary.width-1440-300x61.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F16092409%2F03-PS-Sankariah-Nine_decades_a_revolutionary.width-1440-1024x207.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-684994%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22243%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20school%20in%20Thoothukudi%20town%20(left)%20that%20Sankariah%20attended%20upto%20Class%205.%20He%20later%20completed%20schooling%20at%20St.%20Mary%E2%80%99s%20(middle)%20in%20Madurai.%20And%20then%20on%20to%20The%20American%20College%20(right)%2C%20Madurai%20for%20a%20BA%20that%20he%20never%20completed.%20He%20was%20jailed%2015%20days%20before%20his%20final%20exams.%20Photo%3A%20M.%20Palanikumar%2C%20Surya%20Art%20Photography%2F%20People%E2%80%99s%20Archive%20of%20Rural%20India%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20Sankariah%E2%80%99s%20contemporaries%20in%20the%20American%20College%20%E2%80%93%20and%20in%20the%20larger%20students%E2%80%99%20movement%20%E2%80%93%20would%20become%20prominent%20figures%20after%20graduation.%20One%20went%20on%20to%20become%20the%20chief%20secretary%20of%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20another%20a%20judge%2C%20a%20third%20an%20IAS%20officer%20who%20was%20secretary%20to%20a%20chief%20minister%20decades%20ago.%20Sankariah%20went%20on%20to%20frequent%20more%20jails%20and%20prisons%20%E2%80%93%20even%20after%20Independence.%20Among%20the%20jails%20he%20saw%20from%20the%20inside%20before%201947%20%E2%80%93%20Madurai%2C%20Vellore%2C%20Rajahmundry%2C%20Kannur%2C%20Salem%2C%20Thanjavur%E2%80%A6.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20Communist%20Party%20banned%20in%201948%2C%20he%20went%20underground%20once%20more.%20He%20was%20arrested%20in%201950%20and%20released%20a%20year%20later.%20In%201962%2C%20he%20was%20among%20many%20communists%20jailed%20%E2%80%93%20in%20his%20case%2C%20for%207%20months%20%E2%80%93%20at%20the%20time%20of%20the%20India-China%20war.%20In%20yet%20another%20crackdown%20on%20the%20communist%20movement%20in%201965%2C%20he%20spent%20a%20further%2017%20months%20in%20jail.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%E2%80%99s%20a%20remarkable%20lack%20of%20bitterness%20towards%20those%20who%20targeted%20him%20after%20Independence.%20As%20far%20he%20is%20concerned%2C%20those%20were%20political%20battles%2C%20not%20personal%20ones.%20And%20his%20was%20and%20remains%20a%20fight%20for%20the%20wretched%20of%20the%20earth%2C%20with%20no%20thought%20of%20personal%20gain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20were%20for%20him%20the%20turning%20points%2C%20or%20inspirational%20moments%20of%20the%20freedom%20struggle%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBhagat%20Singh%E2%80%99s%20execution%20%5BMarch%2023%2C%201931%5D%20by%20the%20British%2C%20of%20course.%20The%20Indian%20National%20Army%20%5BINA%5D%20trials%20starting%201945%2C%20and%20the%20Royal%20Indian%20Navy%20%5BRIN%5D%20Mutiny%20of%201946.%E2%80%9D%20These%20were%20%E2%80%9Camong%20the%20main%20events%20that%20gave%20the%20battle%20against%20British%20imperialism%20greater%20momentum.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThrough%20the%20decades%2C%20his%20involvement%20in%20and%20commitment%20to%20the%20Left%20grew%20deeper.%20He%20would%20be%20forever%2C%20a%20wholetimer%20of%20his%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%201944%20I%20was%20released%20from%20Thanjavur%20jail%20and%20was%20selected%20as%20the%20Madurai%20district%20committee%20secretary%20of%20the%20Communist%20Party%20of%20India.%20And%20for%2022%20years%2C%20I%20was%20elected%20as%20the%20state%20committee%20secretary%20of%20the%20Party.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F16092432%2F04b-2014-JULY-15-4-PS-Sankariah-Nine_decad.max-1400x1120-1.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F16092432%2F04b-2014-JULY-15-4-PS-Sankariah-Nine_decad.max-1400x1120-1.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F16092432%2F04b-2014-JULY-15-4-PS-Sankariah-Nine_decad.max-1400x1120-1-300x196.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F16092432%2F04b-2014-JULY-15-4-PS-Sankariah-Nine_decad.max-1400x1120-1-1024x669.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-684996%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22784%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EWith%20his%20wife%20S.%20Navamani%20Ammal%20in%202014%20on%20his%2093rd%20birthday.%20Navamani%20Ammal%20passed%20away%20in%202016.%20Photo%3A%20S.%20Gavaskar%2F%20People%E2%80%99s%20Archive%20of%20Rural%20India%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESankariah%20was%20a%20key%20figure%20in%20mass%20mobilisation.%20Madurai%20was%2C%20by%20the%20mid-1940s%2C%20a%20major%20base%20for%20the%20Left.%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20P.C.%20Joshi%20%5BCPI%20general%20secretary%5D%20came%20to%20Madurai%20in%201946%2C%20the%20meeting%20was%20attended%20by%201%20lakh%20people.%20Many%20of%20our%20meetings%20were%20drawing%20huge%20crowds.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETheir%20growing%20popularity%20led%20the%20British%20to%20foist%20what%20came%20to%20be%20known%20as%20the%20%E2%80%98Madurai%20conspiracy%20case%E2%80%99%20against%20P.%20Ramamurti%20%5Brenowned%20communist%20party%20leader%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu%5D%20as%20first%20accused%2C%20Sankariah%20as%20second%20accused%2C%20and%20several%20other%20CPI%20leaders%20and%20activists.%20They%20were%20charged%20conspiring%20at%20their%20office%20to%20murder%20other%20trade%20union%20leaders.%20The%20chief%20witness%20was%20a%20cart-puller%20who%2C%20police%20said%2C%20just%20happened%20to%20overhear%20them%20and%20dutifully%20reported%20it%20to%20the%20authorities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20N.%20Rama%20Krishnan%20(Sankariah%E2%80%99s%20younger%20brother)%20puts%20it%20in%20his%202008%20biography%C2%A0%3Cem%3EP.%20Ramamurti%20%E2%80%93%20A%20Centenary%20Tribute%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3A%20%E2%80%9CDuring%20the%20enquiry%2C%20Ramamurti%20%5Bwho%20argued%20the%20case%20for%20himself%5D%20proved%20that%20the%20main%20witness%20was%20a%20cheat%20and%20a%20petty%20thief%20who%20had%20undergone%20jail%20sentences%20in%20various%20cases.%E2%80%9D%20The%20special%20judge%20who%20heard%20the%20case%20%E2%80%9Ccame%20to%20the%20jail%20premises%20on%20August%2014%2C%201947%E2%80%A6released%20all%20those%20involved%20in%20the%20case%20and%20severely%20criticised%20the%20government%20for%20launching%20this%20case%20against%20respected%20leaders%20of%20the%20workers.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20have%20been%20strange%20echoes%20of%20that%20past%20in%20recent%20years%20%E2%80%93%20though%20it%E2%80%99s%20unlikely%20in%20our%20time%20we%E2%80%99ll%20find%20a%20special%20judge%20going%20down%20to%20the%20prison%20to%20free%20the%20innocent%20and%20flay%20the%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20CPI%20was%20banned%20in%201948%2C%20Ramamurti%20and%20others%20were%20again%20jailed%20%E2%80%93%20this%20time%20in%20Independent%20India.%20Elections%20were%20coming%20up%2C%20and%20the%20popularity%20of%20the%20Leftists%20was%20a%20threat%20to%20the%20ruling%20Congress%20party%20in%20Madras%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F16092510%2F05a-DSC_0666-PS-Sankariah-Nine_decades_a_r.max-1400x1120-1.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F16092510%2F05a-DSC_0666-PS-Sankariah-Nine_decades_a_r.max-1400x1120-1.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F16092510%2F05a-DSC_0666-PS-Sankariah-Nine_decades_a_r.max-1400x1120-1-300x229.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F16092510%2F05a-DSC_0666-PS-Sankariah-Nine_decades_a_r.max-1400x1120-1-1024x781.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-684998%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22915%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EDMK%20leader%20M.K.%20Stalin%20greeting%20Sankariah%20on%20his%2098th%20birthday%20in%202019.%20Photo%3A%20S.%20Gavaskar%2F%20People%E2%80%99s%20Archive%20of%20Rural%20India%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F16092457%2F05b-2018-APRIL-18-5-PS-Sankariah-Nine_deca.max-1400x1120-1.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F16092457%2F05b-2018-APRIL-18-5-PS-Sankariah-Nine_deca.max-1400x1120-1.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F16092457%2F05b-2018-APRIL-18-5-PS-Sankariah-Nine_deca.max-1400x1120-1-300x229.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F16092457%2F05b-2018-APRIL-18-5-PS-Sankariah-Nine_deca.max-1400x1120-1-1024x781.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-684997%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22915%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESankariah%20and%20V.S.%20Achuthanandan%2C%20the%20last%20living%20members%20of%20the%2032%20who%20walked%20out%20of%20the%20CPI%20National%20Council%20meeting%20in%201964%2C%20being%20felicitated%20at%20that%20party%E2%80%99s%2022nd%20congress%20in%202018%20by%20party%20General%20Secretary%20Sitaram%20Yechury.%20Photo%3A%20S.%20Gavaskar%2F%20People%E2%80%99s%20Archive%20of%20Rural%20India%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSo%20Ramamurti%20filed%20his%20nomination%20while%20in%20detention%2C%20before%20the%20superintendent%20of%20the%20central%20jail.%20He%20contested%20the%201952%20election%20to%20the%20Madras%20Assembly%20from%20Madurai%20North%20constituency.%20I%20was%20in%20charge%20of%20his%20campaign.%20The%20other%20two%20candidates%20were%20Chidambaram%20Bharati%2C%20a%20veteran%20congressman%2C%20and%20P.T.%20Rajan%20from%20the%20Justice%20Party.%20Ramamurti%20won%20handsomely%2C%20the%20result%20was%20announced%20while%20he%20was%20still%20in%20jail.%20Bharati%20came%20second%20and%20Rajan%20lost%20his%20deposit.%20The%20victory%20meeting%20drew%20over%203%20lakh%20people%20to%20celebrate%20the%20win.%E2%80%9D%20Ramamurti%20emerged%20the%20first%20leader%20of%20the%20opposition%20in%20the%20Tamil%20Nadu%20Assembly%20after%20Independence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20communist%20party%20split%20in%201964%2C%20Sankariah%20went%20with%20the%20newly%20formed%20CPI-M.%20%E2%80%9CFrom%20the%2032%20members%20who%20walked%20out%20of%20the%20CPI%20National%20Council%20in%201964%2C%20myself%20and%20V.%20S.%20Achuthanandan%20are%20the%20only%20two%20members%20still%20alive%20today.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0Sankariah%20went%20on%20to%20become%20general%20secretary%20and%20later%20president%20of%20the%20All%20India%20Kisan%20Sabha%2C%20still%20the%20largest%20farmers%20organisation%20in%20India%20with%2015%20million%20members.%20He%20also%20served%20as%20the%20CPI-M%20Tamil%20Nadu%20state%20secretary%20for%20seven%20years%20and%20on%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20central%20committee%20for%20over%20two%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20is%20proud%20of%20the%20fact%20that%20%E2%80%9CWe%20were%20the%20first%20to%20introduce%20Tamil%20in%20the%20Tamil%20Nadu%20assembly.%20In%201952%2C%20there%20was%20no%20provision%20to%20speak%20in%20Tamil%20in%20the%20assembly%2C%20English%20was%20the%20only%20language%2C%20but%20%5Bour%20MLAs%5D%20Jeevanandam%20and%20Ramamurthy%20spoke%20in%20Tamil%20though%20the%20provision%20for%20it%20came%20only%206%20or%207%20years%20later.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESankariah%E2%80%99s%20commitment%20to%20the%20working%20class%20and%20peasantry%20remains%20undiminished.%20He%20believes%20the%20communists%20will%20%E2%80%9Cfind%20the%20correct%20answers%20to%20electoral%20politics%E2%80%9D%20and%20build%20mass%20movements%20on%20a%20greater%20scale.%20An%20hour%20and%20a%20half%20into%20the%20interview%2C%20the%2099-year-old%20is%20still%20talking%20with%20the%20same%20passion%20and%20energy%20with%20which%20he%20began.%20His%20spirit%20remains%20that%20of%20the%209-year-old%20who%20took%20to%20the%20streets%20inspired%20by%20the%20sacrifice%20of%20Bhagat%20Singh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ENote%3A%20My%20thanks%20to%20Kavitha%20Muralidharan%20for%20her%20invaluable%20inputs%20in%20the%20making%20of%20this%20story.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3