e%20start%20provided%20by%20Rohit%20Sharma%20and%20Shubman%20Gill%20and%20the%20seven-wicket%20spell%20by%20the%20unplayable%20Mohammed%20Shami%20all%20proved%20decisive%20in%20India's%20entry%20into%20the%20final.%20But%20among%20all%20those%20names%2C%20one%20that%20stands%20out%20for%20former%20England%20skipper%20Nasser%20Hussain%20is%20the%20skipper.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20SPORTS%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fsports%2Fcricket%2Ficc-world-cup%2Fnews%2Fworld-cup-headlines-may-be-about-virat-kohli-mohammed-shami-but-the-actual-hero-is-%2Farticleshow%2F105248466.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Subrata%20Roy%20Foretold%20New%20India%E2%80%99s%20New%20Crony%20Capitalism%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F16085101%2FUntitled-design-5-1.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20death%20of%20Subrata%20Roy%20of%20the%20Sahara%20Group%20provides%20a%20much-needed%20occasion%20to%20meditate%20on%20the%20inseparability%20of%20the%20business%20community%20and%20the%20political%20class%20in%20modern%20India.%20Saharashri%2C%20as%20Roy%20called%20himself%2C%20came%20to%20personify%20a%20key%20facet%20of%20our%20political%20economy%3A%20that%20money%20power%20can%20thrive%20and%20prosper%20only%20if%20friendly%20%E2%80%98political%20power%E2%80%99%20is%20available.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERecall%20the%20closing%20days%20of%20Shining%20India.%20It%20is%20February%202004.%20The%20saffron%20crowd%20had%20convinced%20itself%20that%20it%20was%20coming%20back%20to%20power%20for%20another%20five%20years%20in%20a%20few%20months.%20And%20Saharashri%20had%20decided%20to%20use%20the%20occasion%20of%20the%20weddings%20of%20both%20his%20sons%20to%20showcase%20his%20connectivity%20with%20political%20players%20of%20all%20hues.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22281%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F04%2F04192003%2Fstatecraft.png%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-237577%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22233%5C%22%3EPrime%20Minister%20A.B.%20Vajpayee%20travelled%20in%20an%20Air%20Force%20plane%20to%20Lucknow%20for%20the%20Sahara%20wedding%3B%20deputy%20prime%20minister%2C%20L.K.%20Advani%20was%20not%20one%20to%20sit%20out%3B%20many%20central%20ministers%20like%20Murli%20Manohar%20Joshi%20and%20Rajnath%20Singh%20felt%20obliged%20to%20honour%20the%20invite%3B%20even%20the%20vice%20president%20of%20India%2C%20Bhairon%20Singh%20Shekhawat%2C%20unmindful%20of%20the%20protocol%20and%20dignity%20of%20his%20high%20office%2C%20allowed%20himself%20to%20be%20persuaded%20to%20attend%3B%20chief%20ministers%20like%20Mulayam%20Singh%20Yadav%20and%20Laloo%20Prasad%20came%3B%20and%2C%20so%20did%20Congress%20leaders%20like%20Digvijay%20Singh%2C%20Ahmed%20Patel%20and%20Murli%20Deora.%20Only%20two%20leaders%20of%20some%20consequence%2C%20Sonia%20Gandhi%20and%20Manmohan%20Singh%20chose%20not%20to%20put%20in%20an%20appearance%20(despite%20many%20entreaties%20and%20pleadings).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOnly%20a%20few%20months%20earlier%2C%20Vajpayee%20had%20warned%20against%20the%20possibility%20of%20%E2%80%98loktantra%E2%80%99%20degenerating%20into%20a%20%E2%80%98dhantantra.%E2%80%99%20But%20the%20Saharashri%20had%20managed%20to%20stage%20an%20intimate%20moment%20in%20the%20uncertain%20relationship%20between%20the%20business%2Findustrial%20class%20and%20the%20political%20crowd%3B%20neither%20side%20felt%20apologetic%20about%20the%20company%20it%20was%20keeping.%20But%20that%20evening%20was%20to%20become%20a%20reminder%20of%20how%20money%20power%20often%20became%20dependent%20upon%20the%20vicissitudes%20of%20a%20changing%20political%20landscape.%20From%20the%20pinnacle%20of%20his%20fame%20and%20respectability%20in%20February%202004%2C%20the%20%E2%80%98entrepreneur%E2%80%99%20who%20died%20in%20a%20Mumbai%20hospital%20ended%20up%20a%20forgotten%20figure%20because%20the%20political%20economy%20chessboard%20got%20reset%20and%20new%20political%20winners%20came%20in%20with%20their%20own%20business%20friends%20and%20financiers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAdmittedly%2C%20the%20business%20community%20has%20a%20legitimate%20stake%20in%20how%20society%20gets%20organised%20and%20how%20it%20is%20governed.%20The%20Indian%20business%20community%2C%20from%20the%20very%20beginning%2C%20has%20sought%20a%20voice%20for%20itself%20in%20shaping%20the%20nation%E2%80%99s%20collective%20future.%20As%20early%20as%20January%201945%2C%20even%20before%20India%20became%20independent%2C%20eight%20business%20leaders%20%E2%80%93%20J.R.D.%20Tata%2C%20G.D.%20Birla%2C%20Sir%20Ardeshir%20Rustomjee%20Dalal%2C%20Sir%20Purshottamdas%20Thakurdas%2C%20Ardeshir%20Darabshaw%2C%20Lala%20Shri%20Ram%2C%20Kasturbhai%20Lalbhai%20and%20Dr.%20John%20Mathai%20%E2%80%93%20had%20proposed%20what%20came%20to%20be%20known%20as%20the%20Bombay%20Plan%2C%20a%20blueprint%20for%20economic%20development.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitical-economy%2Fcrony-capitalism-on-modis-watch-means-invisible-hands-ensure-you-never-go-bankrupt%5C%22%3ECrony%20Capitalism%20on%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20Watch%20Means%20Invisible%20Hands%20Ensure%20You%20Never%20Go%20Bankrupt%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20post-Independence%20leadership%2C%20awash%20as%20it%20was%20in%20the%20legitimacy%20of%20a%20mass%20freedom%20struggle%2C%20did%20not%20much%20care%20for%20the%20Bombay%20Planners%E2%80%99%20advice%20(%20though%20John%20Mathai%20did%20get%20inducted%20very%20early%20in%20Nehru%E2%80%99s%20cabinet%20as%20finance%20minister).%20The%20Bombay%20Plan%20crowd%20liked%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20economic%20intervention%20created%20infrastructure%20they%20were%20not%20capable%20of%20generating%20but%20they%20were%20not%20overly%20amused%20by%20Nehru%E2%80%99s%20attempt%20to%20build%20an%20egalitarian%20social%20order%2C%20with%20%E2%80%98socialistic%E2%80%99%20content.%20Of%20course%2C%20the%20business%20groups%20were%20savvy%20enough%20to%20rejig%20their%20resources%20and%20prejudices%20to%20the%20politicians%E2%80%99%20need%20for%20funds.%20The%20business%20community%20was%20pragmatic%20enough%20to%20recognise%2C%20if%20not%20respect%2C%20the%20sanctity%20of%20democratic%20mandates.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%201971%20Lok%20Sabha%20election%20(post-bank%20nationalisation%20and%20the%20abolition%20of%20privy%20purses)%20was%20perhaps%20the%20only%20time%20when%20the%20business%20leaders%20felt%20agitated%20enough%20to%20openly%20cross%20swords%20with%20sections%20of%20the%20political%20class.%20Industrialists%20like%20K.K.%20Birla%20and%20Naval%20Tata%20entered%20the%20electoral%20arena%20against%20Indira%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20Congress.%20Once%20again%2C%20they%20adjusted%20to%20political%20realities%3B%20and%20the%20Indira%20Gandhi%20regime%2C%20on%20its%20part%2C%20did%20not%20try%20to%20carry%20out%20any%20kind%20of%20vendetta%20against%20recalcitrant%20industrialists.%20Soon%20the%20various%20chambers%20of%20commerce%20were%20ordering%20the%20second%20and%20revised%20edition%20of%20the%20book%20of%20protocol%20of%20crony%20capitalism.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20following%20two%20decades%20%E2%80%93%20before%20Narasimha%20Rao%20and%20Manmohan%20Singh%20unleashed%20India%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98animal%20spirits%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20the%20political%20leaders%E2%80%99%20need%20and%20appetite%20for%20funds%20(for%20party%20and%20personal%20coffers)%20acquired%20a%20definite%20momentum%20and%20a%20certain%20grudging%20acceptability.%20The%20Dhirubhai%20Syndrome%20was%20to%20get%20consecrated.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%201991%2C%20Corporate%20India%20came%20of%20age.%20The%20politicians%20not%20only%20vacated%20the%20economy%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98commanding%20heights%E2%80%99%20but%20they%20also%20stepped%20down%20from%20their%20high%20moral%20perch.%20The%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Edesi%20seths%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20were%20now%20joined%20by%20unscrupulous%20global%20%E2%80%98investors%E2%80%99%20in%20creating%20new%20political%20players%20with%20needs%20and%20greed.%20Governmental%20%E2%80%98stability%E2%80%99%20had%20to%20be%20orchestrated.%20Businessmen%20were%20needed%20with%20whom%20the%20politicians%E2%80%99%20ill-gotten%20funds%20could%20be%20parked.%20And%2C%20a%20political%20leader%E2%80%99s%20association%20with%20shady%20businessman%20was%20not%20looked%20down%20upon%20because%20governmental%20%E2%80%98stability%E2%80%99%20had%20to%20be%20purchased.%20The%20whole%20business%20of%20electoral%20democracy%20became%20exponentially%20expensive.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20new%20nexus%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fqz.com%2Findia%2F248685%2Fraghuram-rajan-explains-why-corrupt-politicians-win-elections-in-india%5C%22%3Ewas%20dissected%20insightfully%20by%20Raghuram%20Rajan%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20%E2%80%9CSo%20the%20circle%20is%20complete.%20The%20crooked%20politician%20needs%20the%20businessman%20to%20provide%20the%20funds%20that%20allow%20him%20to%20supply%20patronage%20to%20the%20poor%20and%20fight%20elections.%20The%20corrupt%20businessman%20needs%20the%20crooked%20politician%20to%20get%20public%20resources%20and%20contracts%20cheaply.%20And%20the%20politician%20needs%20the%20votes%20of%20the%20poor%20and%20the%20under-privileged.%20Every%20constituency%20is%20to%20the%20other%20in%20a%20cycle%20of%20dependency.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESaharashri%20would%20have%20recognised%20the%20%E2%80%98cycle%20of%20dependency%E2%80%99%20that%20Raghuram%20Rajan%20was%20talking%20about.%20Just%20as%20he%20would%20recognise%20that%20even%20in%20%E2%80%98New%20India%E2%80%99%20that%20cycle%20remains%20not%20only%20unbroken%20but%20has%20been%20refined%20and%20almost%20institutionalised.%20Crony%20capitalism%20now%20goes%20by%20a%20new%20name%20called%20%E2%80%98Vikas.%E2%80%99%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fhkhare%5C%22%3EHarish%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fhkhare%5C%22%3EKhare%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20former%20editor-in-chief%20of%20%3C%2Fem%3EThe%20Tribune%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700105080000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F16085101%2FUntitled-design-5-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbusiness%2Fsubrata-roy-foretold-new-indias-new-crony-capitalism%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22'The%20crooked%20politician%20needs%20the%20businessman%20to%20provide%20the%20funds%20that%20allow%20him%20to%20supply%20patronage%20to%20the%20poor%20and%20fight%20elections.%20The%20corrupt%20businessman%20needs%20the%20crooked%20politician%20to%20get%20public%20resources%20and%20contracts%20cheaply.'%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A17%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbusiness%2Fsubrata-roy-foretold-new-indias-new-crony-capitalism%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22KWK%3A%20Kareena%20Kapoor's%20Boss%20Reply%20On%20%26quot%3BHistory%26quot%3B%20With%20Ameesha%20Patel%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EKareena%20Kapoor%20found%20herself%20put%20somewhat%20on%20the%20spot%20by%20host%20Karan%20Johar%20in%20the%20new%20episode%20of%20his%20show%20%3Cem%3EKoffee%20With%20Karan%208%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Kareena%2C%20who%20appeared%20on%20the%20show%20with%20Alia%20Bhatt%2C%20was%20asked%20by%20KJo%20why%20she%20didn't%20attend%20the%20party%20to%20celebrate%20the%20super%20success%20of%20%3Cem%3EGadar%202%3C%2Fem%3E%20held%20earlier%20this%20year.%20%3Cem%3EGadar%202%