20UN%20Climate%20Change%20Conference%20(COP28)%20is%20scheduled%20to%20take%20place%20in%20Dubai.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ENDC%20synthesis%20reports%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%202015%20Paris%20Agreement%20%E2%80%93%20which%20India%20is%20also%20signatory%20to%20%E2%80%93%20mandates%20that%20each%20party%20should%20prepare%2C%20communicate%20and%20maintain%20nationally%20determined%20contributions%20(NDCs)%20that%20it%20intends%20to%20achieve%20to%20adapt%20to%20and%20mitigate%20the%20impacts%20of%20climate%20change.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EInformation%20on%20targets%2C%20policies%20and%20measures%20to%20reduce%20national%20emissions%20and%20adapt%20to%20climate%20change%20impacts%20are%20listed%20in%20annual%20%E2%80%98NDC%20synthesis%20reports%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThese%20reports%20are%20released%20by%20the%20UN%20Framework%20Convention%20on%20Climate%20Change%20%E2%80%93%20which%20has%20been%20adopted%20by%20198%20parties%20including%20India%20%E2%80%93%20which%20aims%20to%20combat%20%E2%80%9Cdangerous%20human%20interference%20with%20the%20climate%20system%E2%80%9D.%20Its%20secretariat%20analyses%20and%20reviews%20the%20latest%20and%20available%20information%20on%20climate%20change%2C%20apart%20from%20conducting%20several%20exercises%20including%20maintaining%20a%20registry%20of%20every%20country%E2%80%99s%20NDCs.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20February%202021%2C%20it%20released%20the%20first%20analysis%20of%20the%20member%20parties%E2%80%99%20NDCs%2C%20followed%20by%20a%20second%20last%20year.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20year%2C%20the%20UN%20body%20analysed%20168%20NDCs%20of%20195%20parties%20signatory%20to%20the%20Paris%20Agreement%2C%20including%2020%20new%20or%20updated%20NDCs%20submitted%20up%20until%20September%2025%2C%202023.%20It%20projected%20emission%20levels%20resulting%20from%20the%20implementation%20of%20the%20NDCs%20when%20compared%20to%20emission%20scenarios%20assessed%20by%20the%20UN%E2%80%99s%20Intergovernmental%20Panel%20on%20Climate%20Change%20(IPCC).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%20%7C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fg20-why-many-of-the-delhi-declarations-climate-commitments-are-vague%5C%22%3EG20%3A%20Why%20Many%20of%20the%20Delhi%20Declaration%E2%80%99s%20Climate%20Commitments%20Are%20Vague%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMost%20parties%20(95%25)%20provided%20the%20information%20necessary%20for%20%E2%80%9Cclarity%2C%20transparency%20and%20understanding%20of%20their%20NDCs%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20report%20found.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAround%2080%25%20of%20the%20parties%20also%20provided%20information%20on%20adaptation%20strategies.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMost%20(97%25)%20also%20provided%20information%20on%20their%20NDC%20planning%20processes%20and%20%E2%80%9Creferred%20to%20their%20implementation%20plans%2C%20communicating%20information%20on%20their%20institutional%20arrangements%2C%20stakeholder%20engagement%20processes%20and%20policy%20instruments%2C%20including%20legislation%2C%20strategies%2C%20plans%20and%20policies%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20report%20noted.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMore%20than%2090%25%20of%20the%20parties%20identified%20energy%20supply%20as%20a%20specific%20priority%20area%20in%20their%20mitigation%20options%20to%20tackle%20climate%20change.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20noted%20that%20coal-fired%20power%20generation%20was%20the%20single%20largest%20source%20of%20energy-related%20CO%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Csub%3E%3Cspan%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fsub%3E%3Cspan%3E%20emissions%20globally%20in%202021%20(9.7%20gigatonnes%20of%20carbon%20dioxide%20equivalent)%2C%20and%20that%20there%20were%20more%20than%208%2C000%20coal-fired%20power%20plants%20operating%20in%20roughly%2090%20countries%20providing%202%20million%20jobs.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20only%209%25%20of%20parties%20%E2%80%93%20which%20together%20account%20for%20more%20than%2050%25%20of%20the%20total%20global%20electricity%20generation%20from%20coal%20in%202021%20%E2%80%93%20listed%20measures%20such%20as%20replacing%20coal-fired%20power%20plants%20with%20less%20polluting%20alternatives.%20Again%2C%20only%204%25%20of%20parties%20mentioned%20the%20need%20for%20or%20measures%20required%20for%20a%20just%20transition%20for%20communities%20and%20workers%20dependent%20on%20coal.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EActions%20not%20enough%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESimilar%20to%20last%20year%E2%80%99s%20analysis%2C%20this%20year%E2%80%99s%20report%20shows%20that%20while%20emissions%20are%20no%20longer%20increasing%20after%202030%20when%20compared%20to%202019%20levels%2C%20they%20are%20still%20not%20declining%20as%20rapidly%20as%20they%20should.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPer%20the%20report%2C%20even%20if%20the%20latest%20NDCs%20are%20implemented%2C%20they%20will%20still%20increase%20emissions%20by%20about%208.8%25%20when%20compared%20to%202010%20levels.%20This%2C%20the%20UN%20press%20release%20said%2C%20is%20a%20%E2%80%9Cmarginal%20improvement%E2%80%9D%20over%20the%202022%20assessment%2C%20which%20found%20that%20countries%20were%20on%20a%20path%20to%20increase%20emissions%20by%2010.6%25%20by%202030%20compared%20to%202010%20levels.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F05%2F15195900%2Fglobal-warming_India_summer-heat-1024x679.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Global%20warming.%20Credit%3A%20Jorge%20Vasconez%2FUnsplash%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22840%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F05%2F15195900%2Fglobal-warming_India_summer-heat-1024x679.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F05%2F15195900%2Fglobal-warming_India_summer-heat-300x199.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F05%2F15195900%2Fglobal-warming_India_summer-heat-768x509.jpg%20768w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-249614%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22557%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EScientists%20have%20said%202023%20is%20on%20track%20to%20be%20the%20warmest%20year%20on%20record%2C%20around%201.4%20%C2%B0C%20above%20pre-industrial%20average%20temperatures.%20Credit%3A%20Jorge%20Vasconez%2FUnsplash.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBy%202030%2C%20emissions%20are%20projected%20to%20be%202%25%20below%202019%20levels%2C%20highlighting%20that%20the%20peaking%20of%20global%20emissions%20will%20occur%20within%20this%20decade.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20order%20to%20achieve%20the%20peaking%20of%20emissions%20before%202030%2C%20the%20report%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20conditional%20elements%20of%20the%20NDCs%20need%20to%20be%20implemented%2C%20which%20depends%20mostly%20on%20access%20to%20enhanced%20financial%20resources%2C%20technology%20transfer%20and%20technical%20cooperation%2C%20and%20capacity-building%20support%3B%20as%20well%20as%20the%20availability%20of%20market-based%20mechanisms.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20latest%20science%20from%20the%20IPCC%20indicates%20that%20greenhouse%20gas%20emissions%20need%20to%20be%20cut%20by%2043%25%20by%202030%2C%20compared%20to%202019%20levels%2C%20to%20limit%20temperature%20rise%20to%201.5%20degrees%20Celsius%20by%20the%20end%20of%20this%20century%20and%20avoid%20the%20worst%20impacts%20of%20climate%20change.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CToday%E2%80%99s%20report%20shows%20that%20governments%20combined%20are%20taking%20baby%20steps%20to%20avert%20the%20climate%20crisis.%20And%20it%20shows%20why%20governments%20must%20make%20bold%20strides%20forward%20at%20COP28%20in%20Dubai%2C%20to%20get%20on%20track%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20executive-secretary%20of%20UN%20Climate%20Change%2C%20Simon%20Stiell.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20means%20COP28%20must%20be%20a%20clear%20turning%20point.%20Governments%20must%20not%20only%20agree%20what%20stronger%20climate%20actions%20will%20be%20taken%20but%20also%20start%20showing%20exactly%20how%20to%20deliver%20them.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CNDCs%20remain%20the%20cornerstone%20of%20our%20shared%20vision%20of%20achieving%20the%20Paris%20targets%2C%20including%20keeping%20the%20target%20of%20below%202%20degrees%20and%20aspiring%20to%20limiting%20%5Bthe%5D%20increase%20to%20below%201.5%20degrees%2C%E2%80%9D%20COP27%20president%20and%20Egypt%E2%80%99s%20foreign%20minister%20Sameh%20Shoukry%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20Sharm%20El-Sheikh%20leaders%20discussed%20several%20initiatives%20to%20assist%20us%20to%20reach%20that%20goal%2C%20as%20well%20as%20assist%20the%20Global%20South%20in%20adapting%20their%20economies%20accordingly.%20We%20need%20to%20keep%20the%20momentum%20going%20as%20there%20is%20no%20time%20to%20waste%20or%20lose%20focus%20on%20the%20target.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fwhat-is-cop-and-why-should-i-care%5C%22%3EWhat%20Is%20COP%20and%20Why%20Should%20I%20Care%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ELong-term%20low-emission%20development%20strategies%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20second%20UN%20Climate%20Change%20report%20on%20long-term%20low-emission%20development%20strategies%2C%20also%20released%20on%20November%2014%2C%20looked%20at%20countries%E2%80%99%20plans%20to%20transition%20to%20net-zero%20emissions%20by%20or%20around%20mid-century.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%2C%20per%20a%20press%20release%2C%20indicated%20that%20these%20countries%E2%80%99%20greenhouse%20gas%20emissions%20could%20be%20roughly%2063%25%20lower%20in%202050%20than%20in%202019%2C%20if%20all%20the%20long-term%20strategies%20are%20fully%20implemented%20on%20time.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECurrent%20long-term%20strategies%20(representing%2075%20parties%20to%20the%20Paris%20Agreement)%20account%20for%2087%25%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20GDP%2C%2068%25%20of%20the%20global%20population%20in%202019%20and%20around%2077%25%20of%20global%20greenhouse%20gas%20emissions%20in%202019%2C%20per%20the%20report.%20This%20is%20a%20strong%20signal%20that%20the%20world%20is%20starting%20to%20aim%20for%20net-zero%20emissions.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20also%20notes%2C%20however%2C%20that%20many%20net-zero%20targets%20remain%20uncertain%20and%20postpone%20into%20the%20future%20critical%20action%20that%20needs%20to%20take%20place%20immediately.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700063145000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F12%2F28202110%2Frefinery.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Finsufficient-progress-in-limiting-temperature-rise-and-tackling-climate-change-says-un-report%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20report%2C%20which%20was%20released%20on%20November%2014%2C%20shows%20that%20while%20emissions%20are%20no%20longer%20increasing%20after%202030%20when%20compared%20to%202019%20levels%2C%20they%20are%20still%20not%20declining%20as%20rapidly%20as%20they%20should.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Finsufficient-progress-in-limiting-temperature-rise-and-tackling-climate-change-says-un-report%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ukraine%20war%3A%20Russian%20diamonds%20set%20for%20ban%20under%20new%20EU%20sa