criminalisation%20of%20adultery%20and%20retain%20Section%20377.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlong%20with%20the%20Bharatiya%20Nyaya%20Sanhita%20Bill%2C%20the%20Bharatiya%20Sakshya%20Adhiniyam%20Bill%20(to%20replace%20the%20Indian%20Evidence%20Act%2C%201872)%20and%20the%20Bharatiya%20Nagarik%20Suraksha%20Sanhita%20Bill%20(to%20replace%20the%20Criminal%20Procedure%20Code%2C%201973)%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fsedition-law-repealed-three-new-bills-tabled-in-parliament-to-replace-criminal-laws%5C%22%3Eintroduced%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20parliament%20on%20August%2011.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bills%20were%20then%20referred%20to%20the%2031-member%20Parliamentary%20Standing%20Committee%2C%20headed%20by%20BJP%20MP%20Brij%20Lal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20panel%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fparliamentary-panel-adopts-reports-on-three-criminal-bills-several-dissent-notes-from-opposition%5C%22%3Eadopted%3C%2Fa%3E%20its%20report%20last%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20analyses%20the%20main%20recommendations%20and%20observations%20of%20the%20committee%20on%20the%20Bharatiya%20Nyaya%20Sanhita%20Bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20opposition%20MPs%20had%20written%20in%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fcriminal-bills-opposition-mp-dissent-note-hindi-imposition-copy-paste%5C%22%3Edissent%20notes%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20new%20legislations%20are%20%E2%80%9Clargely%20a%20copy-paste%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20existing%20laws.%20They%20had%20also%20opposed%20their%20Hindi%20names%2C%20flagged%20the%20lack%20of%20consultation%20and%20the%20diversity%20of%20domain%20expert%20opinion%2C%20and%20questioned%20the%20%E2%80%9Chaste%E2%80%9D%20in%20which%20the%20legislations%20are%20being%20introduced.%20Despite%20these%20objections%2C%20the%20committee%20report%20has%20hailed%20the%20new%20Bills.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fcriminal-bills-opposition-mp-dissent-note-hindi-imposition-copy-paste%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Copy%20Paste%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98Hindi%20Imposition%E2%80%99%3A%20What%20Opposition%20MPs%E2%80%99%20Dissent%20Notes%20on%20the%20Criminal%20Bills%20Say%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERetain%20Section%20377%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20committee%20said%20that%20while%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%202018%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-scraps-section-377-majoritarian-views-cannot-dictate-rights-says-cji%5C%22%3Eruled%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3ENavtej%20Singh%20Johar%20v.%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%20case%20that%20Section%20377%20of%20the%20IPC%20is%20in%20violation%20of%20Articles%2014%2C%2015%2C%2019%2C%20and%2021%20of%20the%20Constitution%20of%20India%2C%20the%20law%20remained%20applicable%20in%20cases%20of%20non-consensual%20carnal%20intercourse%20with%20adults%2C%20all%20acts%20of%20carnal%20intercourse%20with%20minors%2C%20and%20acts%20of%20bestiality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20said%20that%20no%20such%20provision%20for%20non-consensual%20sexual%20offences%20against%20males%2C%20females%20and%20transgenders%20and%20for%20bestiality%20has%20been%20made%20in%20the%20Bharatiya%20Nyaya%20Sanhita%20(BNS)%2C%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20committee%20feels%20that%20to%20align%20with%20the%20objectives%20stated%20in%20the%20BNS%E2%80%99s%20Statement%20of%20Objects%20and%20Reasons%2C%20which%20inter%20alia%20highlights%20the%20move%20towards%20gender-neutral%20offences%2C%20it%20is%20mandatory%20to%20reintroduce%20and%20retain%20Section%20377%20of%20the%20IPC.%20The%20Committee%2C%20therefore%2C%20recommends%20the%20government%20to%20include%20Section%20377%20of%20the%20IPC%2C%20in%20the%20proposed%20law%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERetain%20adultery%20as%20a%20gender-neutral%20criminal%20offence%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20committee%20has%20also%20cited%20the%20interests%20of%20gender%20neutrality%20in%20recommending%20that%20Section%20497%20of%20the%20IPC%2C%20which%20was%20struck%20down%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%202018%2C%20should%20be%20retained%20in%20the%20proposed%20legislation%20by%20%E2%80%9Cmaking%20it%20gender-neutral%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20Section%20497%2C%20a%20person%20who%20had%20sexual%20intercourse%20with%20a%20married%20woman%20without%20the%20consent%20or%20connivance%20of%20her%20husband%20would%20be%20guilty%20of%20adultery.%20This%20was%20punishable%20with%20imprisonment%20or%20fine%20or%20both%3B%20but%20the%20woman%20was%20not%20punishable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fshould-adultery-be-a-crime-at-all%5C%22%3EShould%20Adultery%20Be%20a%20Crime%20at%20All%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20while%20striking%20down%20the%20law%20had%20said%20it%20was%20archaic%2C%20arbitrary%2C%20and%20paternalistic%20and%20that%20it%20infringed%20upon%20a%20woman%E2%80%99s%20autonomy%2C%20dignity%2C%20and%20privacy%2C%20and%20that%20it%20reduced%20the%20married%20woman%20to%20being%20her%20husband%E2%80%99s%20property.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20this%20regard%2C%20the%20committee%20is%20of%20the%20view%20that%20the%20institution%20of%20marriage%20is%20considered%20sacred%20in%20Indian%20society%20and%20there%20is%20a%20need%20to%20safeguard%20its%20sanctity.%20For%20the%20sake%20of%20protecting%20the%20institution%20of%20marriage%2C%20this%20section%20should%20be%20retained%20in%20the%20Sanhita%20by%20making%20it%20gender-neutral%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDeath%20penalty%20and%20Hindi%20imposition%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20opposition%20MPs%20in%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fcriminal-bills-opposition-mp-dissent-note-hindi-imposition-copy-paste%5C%22%3Edissent%20notes%3C%2Fa%3E%20had%20highlighted%20the%20need%20to%20abolish%20the%20death%20penalty%20and%20wrote%20against%20the%20Hindi%20names%20of%20the%20three%20laws%2C%20the%20committee%20has%20not%20recommended%20either.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20said%20that%20the%20committee%20had%20considered%20the%20submissions%20on%20doing%20away%20with%20the%20death%20penalty%2C%20but%20left%20the%20matter%20to%20be%20decided%20by%20the%20Union%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20committee%2C%20after%20considering%20the%20submissions%20regarding%20the%20death%20penalty%2C%20has%20understood%20that%20the%20reason%20for%20a%20passionate%20argument%20against%20death%20penalty%20is%20that%20the%20judicial%20system%20can%20be%20fallible%20and%20to%20prevent%20an%20innocent%20person%20from%20being%20wrongly%20sentenced%20to%20death.%20In%20this%20regard%2C%20the%20committee%20recommends%20that%20the%20matter%20may%20be%20left%20for%20the%20government%20to%20consider%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20also%20said%20that%20the%20committee%20was%20satisfied%20with%20the%20arguments%20of%20the%20home%20ministry%20and%20that%20the%20Hindi%20names%20of%20the%20Bills%20are%20not%20a%20violation%20of%20Article%20348%20of%20the%20constitution%2C%20which%20says%20that%20language%20to%20be%20used%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20and%20in%20the%20high%20courts%2C%20as%20well%20as%20for%20Acts%2C%20Bills%20and%20other%20legal%20documents%2C%20shall%20be%20in%20English.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FnpHbecvfc9o%3Fsi%3DeGrjjOE1jn1JXMtC%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20committee%20finds%20that%20as%20the%20text%20of%20the%20Sanhita%20is%20in%20English%2C%20it%20does%20not%20violate%20the%20provisions%20of%20Article%20348%20of%20the%20Constitution.%20The%20Committee%20is%20satisfied%20with%20the%20response%20of%20the%20Ministry%20and%20holds%20that%20the%20name%20given%20to%20the%20proposed%20legislation%20is%20not%20in%20violation%20of%20Article%20348%20of%20the%20Constitution%20of%20India%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDefining%20community%20service%2C%20life%20imprisonment%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20committee%20has%20recommended%20that%20while%20the%20new%20law%20proposes%20to%20change%20the%20definition%20of%20imprisonment%20for%20life%20to%20mean%20it%20as%20imprisonment%20for%20the%20remainder%20of%20a%20person%E2%80%99s%20natural%20life%2C%20the%20courts%20have%20interpreted%20imprisonment%20for%20life%20simpliciter%20to%20mean%20a%20%E2%80%98whole%20life%20sentence%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20committee%20recommends%20that%20suitable%20amendments%20may%20be%20made%20in%20consultation%20with%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Law%20and%20Justice%20to%20make%20clause%204(b)%20more%20comprehensive%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20committee%20also%20noted%20that%20while%20the%20introduction%20of%20community%20service%20is%20a%20welcome%20step%20and%20a%20reformatory%20approach%2C%20the%20%E2%80%9Cterm%20and%20nature%20of%20community%20service%E2%80%9D%20has%20not%20been%20specified%20and%20should%20be%20duly%20defined.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EReplace%20mental%20illness%20with%20unsound%20mind%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20committee%20has%20also%20recommended%20that%20the%20term%20%E2%80%98mental%20illness%E2%80%99%20be%20replaced%20with%20%E2%80%98unsound%20mind%E2%80%99%20in%20the%20Bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20said%20that%20the%20term%20mental%20illness%20is%20too%20wide%20in%20its%20import%20in%20comparison%20to%20unsound%20mind%2C%20as%20it%20appears%20to%20include%20even%20mood%20swings%20or%20voluntary%20intoxication%20within%20its%20ambit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20committee%20is%20also%20of%20the%20view%20that%20such%20a%20frivolous%20claim%2C%20if%20recognised%20as%20a%20valid%20defence%2C%20will%20spell%20doom%20for%20the%20prosecution%20as%20all%20defences%20will%20be%20claimed%20under%20this%20provision%2C%20thereby%20defeating%20the%20very%20purpose%20of%20this%20Sanhita%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERectify%20all%20grammatical%20and%20typographical%20errors%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20committee%20has%20noted%20typographical%20and%20grammatical%20errors%20in%20the%20text%20of%20the%20Bill%20that%20had%20also%20been%20raised%20by%20opposition%20MPs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20committee%20is%20of%20the%20view%20that%20even%20a%20single%20typographical%20or%20grammatical%20error%20in%20the%20Sanhita%20has%20the%20potential%20to%20be%20misinterpreted%20and%20diluting%20the%20intent%20of%20the%20provision.%20The%20committee%2C%20therefore%2C%20recommends%20the%20ministry%20to%20rectify%20such%20typographical%20and%20grammatical%20errors%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%9CRephrasing%E2%80%9D%20sedition%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20Union%20home%20minister%20Amit%20Shah%E2%80%99s%20claims%20in%20parliament%20that%20the%20sedition%20law%20has%20been%20deleted%2C%20opposition%20MPs%20had%20written%20in%20their%20dissent%20notes%20about%20reintroducing%20the%20law%20in%20a%20more%20draconian%20manner.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20committee%20has%2C%20however%2C%20%E2%80%9Ccomplimented%E2%80%9D%20the%20Union%20government%20for%20deleting%20the%20term%20and%20%E2%80%9Crephrasing%20it.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20committee%20compliments%20the%20government%20in%20deleting%20the%20term%20%E2%80%98sedition%E2%80%99%20from%20criminal%20law%20by%20rephrasing%20it%20without%20compromising%20the%20security%20of%20the%20state%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20committee%20finds%20it%20as%20a%20very%20progressive%20development.%20It%20is%20observed%20that%20in%20the%20Explanation%20part%20of%20clause%2C%20due%20to%20a%20typological%20error%20the%20sentence%20remains%20incomplete.%20The%20words%20%E2%80%98do%20not%20constitute%20offence%20under%20this%20section%E2%80%99%20may%20be%20added%20at%20the%20end.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECommittee%20hails%20%E2%80%9Cmilestone%20initiative%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20committee%20has%20hailed%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Cmilestone%20initiative%E2%80%9D%20in%20bringing%20these%20laws.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20opposition%20MPs%20had%20written%20about%20the%20lack%20of%20diversity%20in%20domain%20expert%20opinion%2C%20the%20committee%20said%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20process%20of%20consultation%20undertaken%20has%20been%20exhaustive%20and%20comprehensive%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CA%20comprehensive%20review%20of%20the%20criminal%20justice%20system%20in%20our%20country%20was%20the%20need%20of%20the%20hour%20to%20bring%20it%20on%20par%20with%20the%20contemporary%20aspirations%20of%20the%20people.%20Having%20taken%20a%20citizen-centric%20approach%2C%20these%20proposed%20laws%20serve%20as%20a%20reassurance%20to%20the%20Indian%20citizens.%20The%20committee%20feels%20that%20these%20Bills%20are%20much-awaited%20and%20much-needed%20reforms%20as%20well%20as%20an%20imperative%20for%20smooth%20and%20transparent%20functioning%20of%20our%20legal%20system%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700061324000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F27110211%2FScreenshot-2023-05-27-at-11.00.50-AM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fparliamentary-panel-gender-neutrality-section-377-criminalising-adultery%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Parliamentary%20Standing%20Committee%20on%20Home%20Affairs%2C%20in%20its%20report%20that%20was%20adopted%20last%20week%2C%20has%20given%20its%20recommendations%20for%20the%20Bharatiya%20Nyaya%20S