hat%20asylum%20seekers%20would%20be%20%E2%80%9Cat%20real%20risk%20of%20ill-treatment%E2%80%9D%20because%20they%20could%20be%20sent%20back%20to%20their%20home%20countries%20once%20they%20were%20in%20Rwanda.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20appealed%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20after%20a%20lower%20court%20had%20already%20ruled%20that%20the%20removal%20policy%20to%20the%20East%20African%20country%20was%20unlawful%20because%20Rwanda%C2%A0could%20not%20be%20considered%20a%20safe%20third%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHaving%20been%20taken%20through%20the%20evidence%20we%20agree%20with%20their%20conclusion%2C%E2%80%9D%20a%20five-judge%20panel%20said%20of%20the%20Court%20of%20Appeal%E2%80%99s%20earlier%20decision%2C%20arguing%20there%20was%20a%20%E2%80%9Creal%20risk%E2%80%9D%20to%20asylum%20seekers%E2%80%99%20rights%20under%20international%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20have%20the%20UK%20and%20Rwanda%20said%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EResponding%20to%20the%20decision%2C%20UK%20Prime%20Minister%20Rishi%20Sunak%20said%20in%20a%20statement%3A%20%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20seen%20today%E2%80%99s%20judgment%20and%20will%20now%20consider%20next%20steps.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20added%3A%20%E2%80%9CThis%20was%20not%20the%20outcome%20we%20wanted%2C%20but%20we%20have%20spent%20the%20last%20few%20months%20planning%20for%20all%20eventualities%20and%20we%20remain%20completely%20committed%20to%20stopping%20the%20boats.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESunak%20will%20hold%20a%20press%20conference%20on%20the%20court%20ruling%20later%20on%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20Rwandan%20government%20spokesperson%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CWe%20do%20take%20issue%20with%20the%20ruling%20that%20Rwanda%20is%20not%20a%20safe%20third%20country%20for%20asylum%20seekers%20and%20refugees.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20been%20recognised%20by%20the%20UNHCR%20and%20other%20international%20institutions%20for%20our%20exemplary%20treatment%20of%20refugees.%20Th