0Biden%20and%20Chinese%20President%20Xi%20Jinping%20would%20have%20been%20mapped%20out.%20The%20intricate%20choreography%20highlights%20the%20delicate%20nature%20of%20their%20relations%2C%20with%20both%20sides%20cautious%20in%20not%20raising%20any%20hopes%20of%20any%20substantive%20takeaway%20%E2%80%93%20even%20as%20there%20is%20buzz%20about%20the%20possibility%20of%20reopening%20military%20communication.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20is%20this%20meeting%20significant%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20and%20China%20are%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20two%20largest%20economies%2C%20but%20the%20APEC%20summit%20in%20San%20Francisco%20will%20be%20the%20first%20time%20that%20their%20leaders%20would%20be%20talking%20to%20each%20other%20in%20over%20a%20year.%20Last%20time%2C%20Xi%20and%20Biden%20had%20met%20on%20the%20sidelines%20of%20the%20G-20%20summit%20in%20Bali%20in%20November%202022%20for%20about%20three%20hours.%20The%20US%20leader%20had%20hoped%20to%20talk%20with%20Xi%20during%20the%202023%20G-20%20summit%20in%20India%2C%20but%20the%20Chinese%20President%20was%20a%20no-show%20in%20New%20Delhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20has%20China%20been%20signalling%20its%20intent%20before%20the%20meeting%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20former%20Obama%20administration%20official%20told%20the%20%3Cem%3EWall%20Street%20Journal%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Chinese%20state%20commentaries%20in%20the%20run-up%20to%20the%20visit%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2Fpolitics%2Fwhat-it-took-to-get-biden-and-xi-to-the-table-11699856893247.html%5C%22%3Ehave%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20%E2%80%9Cit%E2%80%99s%20OK%20to%20be%20nice%20to%20the%20Americans%20now.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EXinhua%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20been%20running%20a%20series%20of%20commentaries%20on%20%E2%80%9CBringing%20China-US%20Relations%20Back%20on%20Track%E2%80%9D%2C%20which%20emphasise%20that%20the%20two%20countries%20have%20enough%20common%20ground%20to%20not%20have%20a%20confrontational%20relationship.%20It%20is%20not%20surprising%20that%20all%20of%20them%20blame%20the%20downturn%20in%20relations%20on%20Washington.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhether%20the%20reality%20of%20interdependence%20between%20the%20two%20countries%20has%20been%20ignored%2C%20the%20history%20of%20win-win%20cooperation%20has%20been%20distorted%2C%20channels%20of%20dialogue%20and%20communication%20have%20been%20blocked%2C%20or%20the%20so-called%20%E2%80%9Cstrategic%20competition%E2%80%9D%20has%20been%20used%20to%20define%20and%20influence%20Sino-US%20relations%20in%20a%20dangerous%20way%2C%20it%20has%20brought%20great%20harm%20to%20the%20people%20of%20the%20two%20countries%20and%20the%20world.%20The%20future%20of%20various%20countries%20has%20brought%20huge%20variables.%C2%A0The%20root%20cause%20is%20that%20the%20United%20States%20has%20a%20wrong%20understanding%20of%20China%2C%20the%20world%2C%20and%20itself%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.news.cn%2Fworld%2F2023-11%2F10%2Fc_1129968050.htm%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EXinhua%3C%2Fem%3E%20opinion%20piece%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20November%2010.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThree%20days%20later%2C%20another%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fpaper.people.com.cn%2Frmrb%2Fhtml%2F2023-11%2F12%2Fnw.D110000renmrb_20231112_2-03.htm%5C%22%3Ecommentary%3C%2Fa%3E%20noted%20that%20the%20meeting%20is%20%E2%80%9Csignificant%20for%20truly%20stabilising%20and%20improving%20China-US%20relations%20and%20for%20jointly%20addressing%20global%20challenges%20and%20promoting%20world%20peace%20and%20development%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20fellow%20at%20the%20Council%20for%20Foreign%20Relations%2C%20Ian%20Johnson%2C%20the%20summit%20meeting%20may%20be%20more%20crucial%20for%20Xi%20than%20previously%2C%20because%20he%20has%20been%20through%20a%20rough%20two%20years%2C%20with%20economic%20and%20political%20turmoil%20unusually%20marking%20the%20leadership.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSo%20I%20think%20that%20for%20Xi%20it%20matters%20to%20be%20able%20to%20show%20to%20his%20domestic%20constituents%2C%20people%20in%20the%20Politburo%2C%20that%20he%E2%80%99s%20got%20the%20United%20States%20%E2%80%93%20that%20relations%20aren%E2%80%99t%20spinning%20out%20of%20control%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cfr.org%2Fevent%2Fvirtual-media-briefing-previewing-apec-and-biden-xi-meeting%5C%22%3Ehe%20said%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20are%20the%20US%20administration%E2%80%99s%20expectations%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CManaging%E2%80%9D%20the%20relationship%20seems%20to%20be%20the%20key%20aim%20for%20the%20US%20which%20had%20keenly%20pursued%20a%20Xi-Biden%20meeting%20by%20sending%20four%20senior%20US%20administration%20officials%20to%20Beijing%20over%20several%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Monday%2C%20US%20national%20security%20advisor%20Jake%20Sullivan%20had%20said%20that%20the%20core%20element%20of%20the%20bilateral%20relationship%20is%20now%20about%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.whitehouse.gov%2Fbriefing-room%2Fpress-briefings%2F2023%2F11%2F14%2Fpress-briefing-by-press-secretary-karine-jean-pierre-and-national-security-advisor-jake-sullivan-november-13-2023%2F%5C%22%3Emanaging%20competition%20responsibly%20so%20that%20it%20does%20not%20veer%20into%20conflict%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20foreign%20policy%20fires%20breaking%20out%20all%20over%20the%20globe%20from%20Ukraine%20to%20Gaza%2C%20the%20US%20administration%20will%20need%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20the%20relationship%20with%20China%20does%20not%20add%20fuel%20to%20the%20fire.%20As%20Biden%20goes%20into%20re-election%20year%2C%20it%20will%20be%20important%20to%20maintain%20peace%20on%20some%20fronts%2C%20even%20though%20foreign%20policy%20typically%20does%20not%20emerge%20as%20a%20primary%20voting%20concern%20in%20the%20US%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20are%20expected%20to%20be%20the%20main%20deliverables%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhite%20House%20officials%20have%20informed%20reporters%20that%20there%20won%E2%80%99t%20be%20a%20joint%20statement%2C%20signalling%20a%20modest%20expectation%20in%20terms%20of%20outcomes.%20Instead%2C%20each%20side%20will%20release%20its%20own%20readouts%2C%20focusing%20on%20their%20respective%20key%20concerns.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETill%20now%2C%20the%20US%20side%20has%20largely%20indicated%20that%20there%20could%20be%20one%20concrete%20deliverable.%20White%20House%E2%80%99s%20Sullivan%20had%20specifically%20referred%20to%20%E2%80%9Cre-establishing%20military-to-military%20communications%E2%80%9D%20which%20had%20been%20snapped%20by%20China%20after%20Speaker%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthediplomat.com%2F2023%2F08%2Fsince-the-pelosi-visit-china-has-created-a-new-normal-in-the-taiwan-strait%2F%5C%22%3E%20Nancy%20Pelosi%E2%80%99s%20visit%20to%20Taiwan%20last%20year%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Biden%20had%20also%20said%20that%20it%20will%20be%20his%20%E2%80%9Cgoal%E2%80%9D%20on%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20some%20observers%2C%20Taiwan%20would%20be%20the%20most%20important%20topic%20to%20be%20discussed%20at%20the%20summit.%20China%20is%20likely%20to%20seek%20assurances%20that%20Washington%20will%20not%20back%20any%20particular%20candidate%20in%20the%20upcoming%20elections%20in%20Taiwan%20in%20early%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20US%2C%20an%20agreement%20on%20plugging%20the%20import%20of%20chemicals%20that%20are%20used%20to%20make%20fentanyl%2C%20a%20leading%20cause%20of%20deaths%20due%20to%20opioid%20addiction%2C%20would%20be%20a%20victory%20for%20Biden%2C%20which%20he%20could%20tout%20as%20a%20tangible%20foreign%20policy%20achievement%20that%20will%20impact%20the%20people.%20But%2C%20as%20per%20reports%2C%20China%20has%20linked%20potential%20restrictions%20on%20trade%20of%20precursor%20chemicals%20on%20the%20condition%20that%20the%20US%20has%20to%20lift%20sanctions%20on%20Chinese%20police%20foreign%20institute%20in%20a%20quid-pro-quo%20deal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20South%20China%20Morning%20Post%3C%2Fem%3E%20had%20reported%20earlier%20that%20the%20two%20sides%20are%20expected%20to%20sign%20an%20agreement%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scmp.com%2Fnews%2Fchina%2Fmilitary%2Farticle%2F3241177%2Fbiden-xi-set-pledge-ban-ai-autonomous-weapons-drones-nuclear-warhead-control-sources%5C%22%3Ethe%20use%20of%20artificial%20intelligence%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20autonomous%20weaponry%20and%20control%20and%20deployment%20of%20nuclear%20warheads.%20However%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EFinancial%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%20that%20China%20was%20only%20seeking%20an%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2F908acb66-7e74-4f22-bfae-c842a44b668a%5C%22%3Eexpanded%20dialogue%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20in%20this%20domain%20with%20the%20%E2%80%9Chope%20that%20engagement%20would%20delay%20further%20US%20restrictions%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20and%20China%20have%20diametrically%20opposite%20views%20on%20the%20two%20current%20conflicts%20in%20Ukraine%20and%20the%20Palestinian%20territories.%20Having%20positioned%20itself%20as%20a%20leader%20of%20the%20Global%20South%2C%20Beijing%20is%20unlikely%20to%20find%20much%20common%20ground%20with%20Washington%20on%20these%20geopolitical%20hotspots%2C%20beyond%20giving%20public%20utterances%20about%20the%20need%20to%20contain%20the%20spread%20of%20the%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700058923000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F15194439%2Fimage-1506.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fexplainer-as-xi-biden-meet-after-a-year-both-sides-play-nice-but-expectations-are-low%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20US%20and%20China%20are%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20two%20largest%20economies%2C%20but%20the%20APEC%20summit%20in%20San%20Francisco%20will%20be%20the%20first%20time%20that%20their%20leaders%20would%20be%20talking%20to%20each%20other%20in%20over%20a%20year.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fexplainer-as-xi-biden-meet-after-a-year-both-sides-play-nice-but-expectations-are-low%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20a%20Tribal%20Woman%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98Bamboo%20Kandils%E2%80%99%20Captured%20the%20World%20Stage%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EComing%20from%20a%20small%20village%20called%20Tetwali%20in%20Maharashtra%2C%20Namita%20Namdev%20Bhurkood%20learned%20one%20of%20the%20more%20emphasised%20roles%20growing%20up%20%E2%80%94%20being%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F332396%2Fhow-to-make-bio-enzymes-from-kitchen-waste-at-home-diy-steps-by-kolkata-gardener-nita-singh%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egood%20homemaker.%20%3C%2Fa%3EWhat%20she%20did%20not%20realise%20for%20a%20long%20time%20was%20that%20she%20could%20also%20be%20the%20breadwinner%20of%20a%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20she%20rightly%20puts%20it%2C%20life%20is%20mostly%20about%20%E2%80%9Crediscovering%20yourself%E2%80%9D%20every%20other%20day.%20Now%2C%20she%20finds%20herself%20in%20more%20than%20one%20role%20%E2%80%94%20a%20mother%2C%20a%20homemaker%2C%20a%20bamboo%20artist%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20president%20of%20the%20women%E2%80%99s%20self-help%20group%20in%20the%20village.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20group%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F317348%2Fmangal-shetty-sustainable-home-in-aghanashini-karnataka-panchabhuta-conservation-foundation%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etransforms%20bamboo%20into%20beautiful%20products%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20such%20as%20%3Cem%3Ekandils%3C%2Fem%3E%20(sky%20lanterns)%2C%20phone%20holders%2C%20%3Cem%3Erakhis%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20dustbins%2C%20photo%20frames%2C%20carts%2C%20hangers%2C%20keychains%20and%20much%20more.%20Rec