0class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EPeacock%20The%20King%20of%20Birds%2C%20Picture%20source%3A%20Durgabai%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202000%2C%20Vyam%20expanded%20her%20art%20canvas.%20She%20began%20making%20drawings%20for%20booklets%20published%20by%20the%20Eklavya%20Foundation.%20%E2%80%9COnce%20they%20became%20popular%2C%20I%20was%20approached%20by%20Chennai-based%20Tara%20Books%20for%20the%20same.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20Vyam%20and%20her%20husband%20proudly%20declare%20their%20most%20iconic%20project%20to%20be%20illustrating%20for%20the%20book%20%E2%80%98Bhimayana%3A%20Experiences%20of%20Untouchability%E2%80%99%2C%20which%20chronicles%20the%20life%20and%20times%20of%20Dr%20Babasaheb%20Ambedkar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20this%2C%20the%20couple%20have%20illustrated%20children%E2%80%99s%20novels%2C%20history%20fiction%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F325545%2Fmust-watch-films-and-shows-on-disability-pride-and-representation-in-cinema%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebiographies%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20more.%20In%202008%2C%20Vyam%20was%20awarded%20the%20BolognaRagazzi%20award%20for%20her%20illustrations%20in%20%E2%80%98The%20Night%20Life%20of%20Trees%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20even%20as%20I%20ask%20Vyam%20about%20these%20accolades%2C%20expecting%20an%20elaborate%20answer%2C%20she%20shrugs.%20%E2%80%9CI%20am%20happy.%20The%20awards%20make%20me%20happy.%20It%20is%20a%20great%20feeling%20to%20see%20my%20%3Cem%3Edignas%3C%2Fem%3E%20getting%20so%20much%20love%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20shares.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEdited%20by%20Pranita%20Bhat%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699972262000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D334085%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Bhopal-based%20Gond%20artist%20Durgabai%20Vyam's%20nature-inspired%20art%20and%20culturally-rooted%20motifs%20have%20gained%20national%20and%20international%20acclaim%2C%20earning%20her%20the%20prestigious%20Padma%20Shri%20in%202022.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Krystelle%20Dsouza%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F334085%2Fbhopal-durgabai-vyam-padma-shri-gond-artist-inspiring-story%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Braving%20Threats%20by%20Land%20Mafia%2C%20Techie%20Turns%2025-Acre%20Barren%20Land%20Into%20a%20Forest%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EGrowing%20up%20in%20Gudiyatham%20in%20Vellore%2C%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20G%20Srikanth%20grew%20up%20in%20the%20lap%20of%20nature.%20He%20would%20walk%20to%20school%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F332580%2Fmillet-based-startups-helping-farmers-ragi-jowar-international-year-of-millet%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epassing%20a%20forest%20%3C%2Fa%3Eon%20the%20way%2C%20and%20would%20enjoy%20listening%20to%20the%20chirping%20birds%20and%20insects.%20After%20an%20idyllic%20childhood%2C%20he%20moved%20to%20Chennai%20and%20worked%20as%20an%20assistant%20director%20in%20the%20movies.%20He%20recalls%20coming%20home%20from%20the%20%E2%80%98concrete%20jungle%E2%80%99%20to%20take%20a%20whiff%20of%20fresh%20air.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20years%2C%20every%20visit%20to%20Gudiyatham%20felt%20different.%20Srikanth%20saw%20the%20green%20cover%20reduce%20slowly%3B%20all%20but%20vanishing%20in%20front%20of%20his%20eyes.%20He%20felt%20disheartened%20that%20his%20hometown%20was%20also%20becoming%20like%20a%20big%20city%2C%20devoid%20of%20its%20natural%20beauty.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202017%2C%20a%20tragic%20incident%20changed%20the%20trajectory%20of%20the%20computer%20science%20graduate%E2%80%99s%20life.%20His%20older%20brother%2C%20Sridhar%2C%20died%20in%20an%20accident%2C%20leaving%20Srikanth%20to%20move%20back%20home.%20He%20started%20working%20in%20the%20fields%20with%20his%20father%2C%20a%20farmer.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20he%20worked%20on%20his%20dream%2C%20to%20increase%20the%20green%20cover%20of%20his%20hometown.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStarting%20by%20planting%201%2C000%20trees%20in%202018%2C%20today%20the%2034-year-old%20has%20planted%20over%2015%2C000%20trees%20in%20Vellore%2C%20creating%20three%20forests.%20On%20the%20way%2C%20he%20has%20faced%20threats%20by%20the%20land%20mafia%20and%20politicians%2C%20had%20his%20trees%20cut%2C%20been%20beaten%2C%20but%20nothing%20has%20shaken%20him.%20He%20stands%20firmly%20on%20his%20resolve%20that%20he%20is%20giving%20back%20to%20Mother%20Nature%2C%20and%20will%20continue%20to%20do%20so%2C%20come%20what%20may.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ETransforming%20a%2025-acre%20barren%20land%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2FMy-work-view-16-1699969285.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Srikanth%20transformed%20a%2025%20acre%20land%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2FMy-work-view-16-1699969285.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2FMy-work-view-16-1699969285-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2FMy-work-view-16-1699969285-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2FMy-work-view-16-1699969285-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2FMy-work-view-16-1699969285-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-334096%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20land%20before%20and%20after%20Srikanth%20planted%207%2C000%20trees.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20August%202018%2C%20Srikanth%20started%20planting%201%2C000%20trees%20on%20the%20roadside%20of%20Ulli%20village%20in%20Gudiyatham.%20He%20also%20took%20responsibility%20for%20maintaining%20the%20trees%2C%20and%20in%20six%20short%20months%2C%20they%20grew%20well.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20used%20to%20be%20a%20social%20forest%20on%20the%20banks%20of%20the%20Palar%20river%2C%20that%20I%20would%20cross%20on%20my%20way%20to%20school%20every%20day.%20It%20was%20slowly%20taken%20over%20by%20the%20land%20mafia%20and%20all%20the%20trees%20were%20cut.%20It%20became%20a%20barren%20wasteland%20which%20was%20just%20used%20for%20sand.%20I%20wanted%20to%20restore%20and%20recreate%20that%20forest%2C%20which%20was%20home%20to%20so%20many%20birds%2C%20insects%20and%20monkeys.%20I%20would%20keep%20giving%20petitions%20to%20the%20district%20collector%20every%20week%2C%20but%20to%20no%20avail%2C%E2%80%9D%20Srikanth%20tells%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20concept%20of%20social%20forestry%20is%20to%20involve%20locals%20of%20the%20region%20in%20the%20afforestation%20of%20unused%20wastelands%2C%20and%20to%20also%20protect%20and%20preserve%20them%20from%20rapid%20deforestation.%20%E2%80%9CIn%20a%20social%20forest%2C%20people%20can%20come%20and%20go%20unlike%20a%20reserved%20forest%2C%20where%20no%20one%20is%20allowed%2C%E2%80%9D%20explains%20Srikanth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20saw%20many%20monkeys%20getting%20hurt%20on%20the%20roads%2C%20which%20bothered%20him%20greatly.%20%E2%80%9CMany%20birds%20and%20monkeys%20would%20be%20wounded.%20They%20had%20no%20place%20to%20go%20to%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%201%2C000%20trees%20that%20he%20planted%20grew%20well%2C%20his%20efforts%20were%20noticed%20by%20the%20local%20authorities%20and%20reached%20the%20attention%20of%20then%20collector%2C%20A%20Shanmuga%20Sundaram.%20Srikanth%20recalls%20that%20Sundaram%20of